Subject: [PATCH 04/22] feat(OIDC-Provider): Add clientCredentialsFlow to Oidc
 Provider (#1732)

* feat(OIDC-Provider): Add clientCredentialsFlow to Oidc Provider

Signed-off-by: mfeix <marcel.feix@exxcellent.de>

* docs(OIDC-Provider): Add clientCredentialsFlow documentation to Oidc Provider docs and api

Signed-off-by: mfeix <marcel.feix@exxcellent.de>

* chore(OIDC-Provider): #1732 Add some requested changes for the MR

Signed-off-by: mfeix <marcel.feix@exxcellent.de>

* chore(OIDC-Provider): #1732 Add some requested changes for the MR

Signed-off-by: mfeix <marcel.feix@exxcellent.de>

* chore(OIDC-Provider): #1732 Add missing Setting to allow Flows in Client

Signed-off-by: mfeix <marcel.feix@exxcellent.de>

* chore(OIDC-Provider): #1732 Move authorization Code bool to use a pointer so default value is nil.

This is done so we can use default behavior and define nil as a true value

Signed-off-by: mfeix <marcel.feix@exxcellent.de>

* chore(OIDC-Provider): #1732 Setup tests according to feedback from PR.

Setup so default behaviour is testet implicate in the tests.

Signed-off-by: mfeix <marcel.feix@exxcellent.de>

* chore(OIDC-Provider): #1732 correctly create access token and remove id token.

Because this should be the correct implementation for access tokens.
Since we do not need access to openbao to access userinfo endpoint.

Signed-off-by: mfeix <marcel.feix@exxcellent.de>

